The beaches of the island‚Ä¶ The beach covers the entirety of the Western portion of the island, with rocky shores cutting off the sand. On the Western part, the sand covers the entire coastline with little to no obstructions. Beyond that, the clear water beats against the sand in a rhythmic motion, never ceasing. The sun shines on the island, bringing light to all its inhabitants. It‚Äôs a peaceful scene. Seagulls fly above the ocean, starfish and shells decorate the sand, and even some fish can be seen swimming further out in the sea. The sand itself is a pearly white, having been untouched by human settlement. This beach is probably the nicest one you‚Äôve ever been on; the sand feels perfect under your feet. The water is clear and refreshing to swim in. Interestingly, out around 50 meters in the sea, you‚Äôll find a coral reef, barricading you in. Of course, you could probably try and swim out over the reef, but the water is significantly more dangerous outside of the reef. Beyond the reef, there lies similar islands to the one you are on. The geography is too diverse to be able to tell where you are. Swimming out to those further islands spells death to the inexperienced. Trapped‚Ä¶ Contained here for all eternity. Multiple types of sea life can be seen. Crabs, clams, fish, eels, jellyfish: all those can be seen throughout the beach. All of them clinging to the water. Living in a perfectly balanced ecosystem, undisturbed by humans. (edited)
